<% content_for :title, "Terms | hushpair" %>

<main class="shell legal-shell" id="main-content">
  <section class="card legal-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Terms of Use</p>
    <h1>hushpair Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Effective date: <%= legal_effective_date(:terms) %>. These Terms govern your use of
      hushpair. By using the service, you agree to them.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>What hushpair provides</h2>
    <p>
      hushpair provides temporary text-only chat for private one-to-one conversations. You can create
      a private room and share an invite link, or use anonymous matching to be paired with the next
      available person.
    </p>
    <p>
      hushpair is experimental beta software. Chats are always temporary and may be interrupted. Never
      share sensitive information, emergency information, regulated information, secrets, passwords,
      financial details, or anything you cannot afford to lose or expose.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>Eligibility</h2>
    <p>
      You must be at least 13 years old to use hushpair. If the laws where you live require a higher
      minimum age or additional consent, you are responsible for meeting those requirements.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>You agree not to use hushpair to:</p>
    <ul class="legal-list">
      <li>Harass, threaten, abuse, exploit, or impersonate other people.</li>
      <li>Share unlawful content or use the service for unlawful conduct.</li>
      <li>Spam, flood rooms, or attempt to disrupt the service.</li>
      <li>Collect, solicit, or pressure others to provide personal contact details.</li>
      <li>Probe, scrape, reverse engineer, or interfere with the security or operation of the service.</li>
      <li>Evade rate limits, moderation controls, or access restrictions.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>Rooms, links, and access</h2>
    <p>
      Private chat rooms are temporary and may expire automatically. Invite links and return links are access
      credentials. Anyone with a valid link may be able to join or return to a room until that access
      expires or is invalidated.
    </p>
    <p>
      Some access, including bookmark-style return access, may be limited to the same browser or session
      where it was created. You are responsible for how you share room links. hushpair cannot guarantee
      that a link forwarded beyond the intended recipient will remain private.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>Anonymous matching</h2>
    <p>
      Matching connects you with another available person for a temporary one-to-one chat. Either person
      may end the chat or move on at any time. If a match ends, hushpair may return either participant to
      the matching flow.
    </p>
    <p>
      Matching is not guaranteed. We may limit, delay, expire, cancel, or refuse matches to protect the
      service, reduce abuse, avoid rapid repeat pairings, or handle operational issues.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>Moderation and enforcement</h2>
    <p>
      We may use rate limits, content screening, access restrictions, room expiration, or other safeguards
      to protect the service and its users. We may suspend, restrict, or terminate access to rooms or the
      service when we believe it is reasonably necessary for safety, abuse prevention, legal compliance, or
      operational integrity.
    </p>
    <p>
      Reporting and ending a chat are lightweight safety controls. Because hushpair is designed to minimize
      identity data, reports may not always support follow-up, account-level enforcement, or recovery of
      expired chat content.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Our Privacy Policy explains how we handle data. By using hushpair, you acknowledge that temporary
      processing, storage, and security controls are part of operating a live chat service.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>Not for emergencies</h2>
    <p>
      hushpair is not an emergency service and should not be used for urgent safety, medical, or
      time-critical communications. We cannot guarantee immediate delivery, active monitoring, or
      continuous availability.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>No guarantee of availability</h2>
    <p>
      hushpair is provided on an “as is” and “as available” basis. We do not guarantee uninterrupted access,
